        - iPod/iPhone and USB device content browsing and ‘now playing’ information<br>
        - Simple navigation of the receiver menu</p>
      <p>• Background video (USB - Radio)</p>
      <p>• 17 CINEMA DSP modes</p>
      <p>• ECO mode</p>
      <p>• Reduced standby power consumption</p>
      <p>• Improved auto power down functionality</p>
      <p>• Dolby and DTS HD Audio decoding with CINEMA DSP</p>
      <p>• YPAO automatic speaker calibration</p>
      <p>• Graphic equaliser</p>
      <p>• Compressed Music Enhancer</p>
      <p>• Preset remote control</p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">RX-V475</h4>
    <div class="thecontent"> <br>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V475.jpg"></p>
      <p>*Also available in Black</p>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V475_tech.jpg"></p>
      <h3>Upsell Features over RX-V375:</h3>
      <p>• 115W x 5 (6O, 1 kHz, 0.9% THD)</p>
      <p>• Direct digital connectivity for iPad/iPhone/iPod<br>
        - iPad charging in standby mode</p>
      <p>• Network connection<br>
        - AV Controller with Music Play<br>
        - AirPlay<br>
        - Internet radio<br>
        - Pandora® Internet radio via firmware update<br>
        - DLNA audio streaming<br>
        - WAV and FLAC decoding (up to 192 kHz)</p>
      <p>• Colour On Screen Display (OSD)<br>
        - Internet radio and network audio content browsing and ‘now playing’ information</p>
      <p>• MHL support for high definition audio and video from portable devices</p>
      <p>• 5 in/1 out HDMI with 3D, ARC and CEC</p>
      <p>• HDMI Standby Through with input select</p>
      <p>• CINEMA DSP 3D with Virtual Presence Speaker technology</p>
      <p>• Direct mode for high quality sound reproduction</p>
      <p>• USB DC out for optional accessories</p>
      <p>• Banana plug terminals for all speakers</p>
      <p>• Increased receiver height - 10 mm</p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">RX-V500D</h4>
    <div class="thecontent"> <br>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V500D.jpg" width="100%"></p>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V500D_tech.jpg"></p>
      <h3>Upsell Features over RX-V375:</h3>
      <p>• Digital radio support (DAB+)</p>
      <p>• 100W x 5 (6O, 1 kHz, 0.9% THD)</p>
      <p>• 4 in/1 out HDMI with 3D, ARC and CEC</p>
      <p>• Front USB port<br>
        - Direct digital connection for iPod/iPhone<br>
        - iPod/iPhone charging in standby mode<br>
        - AAC, MP3, WMA and WAV decoding (up to 48 kHz)</p>
      <p>• Mass storage device support (MSC)</p>
      <p>• SCENE with CEC</p>
      <p>• HDMI Device Control</p>
      <p>• 4K pass-through</p>
      <p>• HDMI fast switching</p>
      <p>• Low Jitter PLL</p>
      <p>• Colour On Screen display<br>
        - Multi-language support (English, Japanese, French, German, Spanish, Russian, Italian and Chinese)<br>
        - iPod/iPhone and USB device content browsing and ‘now playing’ information<br>
        - Simple navigation of the receiver menu</p>
      <p>• Background video (USB - Radio)</p>
      <p>• 17 CINEMA DSP modes</p>
      <p>• ECO mode</p>
      <p>• Reduced standby power consumption</p>
      <p>• Improved auto power down functionality</p>
      <p>• Dolby and DTS HD Audio decoding with CINEMA DSP</p>
      <p>• YPAO automatic speaker calibration</p>
      <p>• Graphic equaliser</p>
      <p>• Compressed Music Enhancer</p>
      <p>• Preset remote control</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="one-third column">
    <h4 class="myheadings">RX-V575</h4>
    <div class="thecontent"> <br>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V575.jpg"></p>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V575_tech.jpg"></p>
      <h3>Upsell Features over RX-V475:</h3>
      <p>• 115W x 7 (6O, 1 kHz, 0.9% THD)</p>
      <p>• 7 channel powerful surround sound</p>
      <p>• Assignable amplifiers for bi-amp connection</p>
      <p>• Zone B connectivity for 2 channel audio in a second room</p>
      <p>• Dual subwoofer output</p>
      <p>• Dolby Pro Logic IIx, DD-EX and DTS-ES audio decoding</p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">RX-V675</h4>
    <div class="thecontent"> <br>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V675.jpg"></p>
      <p>*Also available in Black</p>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V675_tech.jpg"></p>
      <h3>Upsell Features over RX-V575:</h3>
      <p>• 90W x 7 (8O, 20 Hz - 20 kHz, 0.09% THD)</p>
      <p>• 6 in/1 out HDMI with 3D, ARC and CEC<br>
        - HDMI front panel input</p>
      <p>• Multi-zone functionality<br>
        - Zone 2 audio Line OUT and Speaker output<br>
        - Additional speaker line out terminals (Zone 2/Front Presence)</p>
      <p>• Intelligent Amplifier Assignment<br>
        - Front Presence, surround back or Zone 2</p>
      <p>• Pure Direct mode, with optional Video On mode</p>
      <p>• 4K Ultra HD video upscaling</p>
      <p>• Analogue to HDMI upconversion</p>
      <p>• 4 EQ modes including ‘manual’ mode</p>
      <p>• YPAO automatic speaker calibration<br>
        - Reflected Sound Control (R.S.C.)</p>
      <p>• Advanced Graphical User Interface (GUI)</p>
      <p>• Album artwork<br>
        - Network audio, iPod/iPhone/iPad, and USB)<br>
        - Multi-language support</p>
      <p>• IR in/out and 12v Trigger</p>
      <p>• Dialogue Level Adjustment</p>
      <p>• Dialogue Lift (including Virtual Dialogue Lift)</p>
      <p>• DSP effect normalisation</p>
      <p>• Virtual CINEMA DSP using AIR SURROUND XTREME</p>
      <p>• Increased receiver height – 10 mm</p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">RX-V775</h4>
    <div class="thecontent"> <br>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V775.jpg"></p>
      <p><img src="images/RX-V775_tech.jpg"></p>
      <h3>Upsell Features over RX-V675:</h3>
      <p>• 95W x 7 (8O, 20 Hz - 20 kHz, 0.09% THD)</p>
      <p>• 6 in/2 out HDMI with 3D, ARC and CEC<br>
        - Dual simultaneous HDMI outputs</p>
      <p>• Dedicated phono input</p>
      <p>• 7.2 multi-channel pre-out</p>
      <p>• Multi-zone functionality<br>
        - Party Mode<br>
        - Zone 2 binding post terminals<br>
        - Zone 2 pre-out (variable volume)</p>
      <p>• YPAO automatic speaker calibration<br>
        - Multipoint measurement</p>
      <p>• Aluminium front panel</p>
    </div>
